Spent a lot of time to find the right fix for angular / exceljs combination. My current issue was related to version **"exceljs": "^4.2.0"**, and **Angular 8**. In production mode received the same error as an author: from **static-xform.js** file of the library and this function

`function _inherits(subClass, superClass) { if (typeof superClass !== "function" && superClass !== null) { throw new TypeError("Super expression must either be null or a function"); } subClass.prototype = Object.create(superClass && superClass.prototype, { constructor: { value: subClass, writable: true, configurable: true } }); if (superClass) _setPrototypeOf(subClass, superClass); }`

My current solution is to import library from the dist folder, because if we use standard import - Angular removes some classes from the final bundle:
```
import {
  Buffer, Column, Row, Workbook, Worksheet, WorksheetView,
} from 'exceljs';
import * as ExcelJS from 'exceljs/dist/exceljs';
import saveAs from 'file-saver';
---
private workbook: Workbook = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
```
Please be careful with the resource - some people are writing about import of the minified version of the library. For me it doesn't work. So the main point **'exceljs/dist/exceljs'**.
